The paper proposes a framework for consistent assessment, comparison, and combination of aspect mining techniques, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of the framework in a publicly available tool, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve the quality of aspect mining results, which could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
